channel.title: Quick Question
channel.description:
What's the code to delete global objects?
Also, once I have this code, where do I put it? Is it OK to place it directly beneath an AddGlobalObj?
Thanks in advance, Syrillia

item.title: Quick Question
item.dc:creator: @Syrillia Syrillia
item.description:
@Syrillia wrote:

Right, some sources don’t have it. You have to add it in after. But, I just downloaded a new source. HellzEnd, so far, it’s great! Can be found here;

http://www.megaupload.com/?d=GMGXLYD1

When you open it, right click compile and then edit. Replace all with this;

@echo off title Solumscape Compiler //change Solumscape to whatever you want. javac *.java pause
[sup]Taking no credit for this. Not mine. Can’t remember where i got it though.[/sup]

It’s short and sweet but it’s simple and it works. That saves you posting later asking advice. Then open your client.java (your new one that is) Ctrl+F and find ‘AddGlobalObj’ keep going until you find a list full of ‘AddGlobalObj’ and there’s loads of objects there. You can just edit these to place objects on the map.

Hope that helped, back to my question! Help!

Syrillia
